title: Google\Cloud\ArtifactRegistry\V1beta2\Repository
name: Repository
description:
A Repository for storing artifacts with a specific format.

Generated from protobuf message google.devtools.artifactregistry.v1beta2.Repository

params.name: data
params.description: Optional. Data for populating the Message object.

params.name: data.maven_config
params.description: Maven repository config contains repository level configuration for the repositories of maven type.

params.name: data.name
params.description: The name of the repository, for example: "projects/p1/locations/us-central1/repositories/repo1".

params.name: data.format
params.description: The format of packages that are stored in the repository.

params.name: data.labels
params.description: Labels with user-defined metadata. This field may contain up to 64 entries. Label keys and values may be no longer than 63 characters. Label keys must begin with a lowercase letter and may only contain lowercase letters, numeric characters, underscores, and dashes.

params.name: data.create_time
params.description: The time when the repository was created.

params.name: data.update_time
params.description: The time when the repository was last updated.

params.name: data.kms_key_name
params.description: The Cloud KMS resource name of the customer managed encryption key that’s used to encrypt the contents of the Repository. Has the form: projects/my-project/locations/my-region/keyRings/my-kr/cryptoKeys/my-key. This value may not be changed after the Repository has been created.
